# Fix Rope Climbing Logic & Movement Oscillation

## Summary
- **Fixed Rope X-Alignment**: Increased engaging distance to 10px.
- **Fixed Climb Down**: Correctly selects "Down" key at rope top.
- **Improved Completion Detection**: Implemented "Wiggle Test" to confirm platform arrival.
- **Fixed Movement Oscillation**: Corrected distance calculation in horizontal movement logic.

## Changes

### 1. Fix Movement Oscillation & Add Logs
**File**: [Services/CharacterMovementController.cs](file:///d:/Full_end/C%23/ArtaleAI/Services/CharacterMovementController.cs)

**Problem**: User reported character constantly moving Left/Right (oscillating) when trying to align X.
**Cause**: The function [MoveToTargetAsync](file:///d:/Full_end/C%23/ArtaleAI/Services/CharacterMovementController.cs#200-329) was passing **Total Distance** (Euclidean) to the movement controller. If the character was vertically far from the target (e.g. `dy=20`), the Total Distance was large (>20). The controller saw "Distance > 10" and engaged **Long Press Mode** (Running), even if the horizontal distance (`dx`) was only 1px. This caused massive overshooting.
**Fix**: Changed the distance parameter to `Math.Abs(dx)` (Horizontal Distance Only). Now, if `dx` is small, it correctly uses **Tap Mode**, preventing oscillation.

**Log Enhancement**: Added `Pos=(x,y) Target=(x,y)` to movement logs as requested.

```csharp
// Before
await PerformGradualMoveAsync(..., (float)distance, ..., "移動");

// After
await PerformGradualMoveAsync(..., (float)Math.Abs(dx), ..., "移動", currentPos, targetPos);
```

### 2. Active Rope Exit Check (Wiggle Test)
**File**: [Services/CharacterMovementController.cs](file:///d:/Full_end/C%23/ArtaleAI/Services/CharacterMovementController.cs)

Added logic to actively verify if the character has left the rope when near the target height.
- **Trigger**: Character is within 8px (updated by user) of target Y.
- **Action**: Pause climbing, press **Right** key for 100ms.
- **Check**: Measure X movement (`deltaX`).
- **Result**:
  - `deltaX > 2.0f`: Character moved horizontally -> Confirmed **Off Rope** (Success). Loop breaks.
  - `deltaX <= 2.0f`: Character stuck horizontally -> Confirmed **On Rope** (or blocked). Climbing continues.

```csharp
if (Math.Abs(currentPos.Y - targetY) < 8.0f && attempts % 10 == 0) // Updated by User
{
    // ... Wiggle Test Implementation ...
    if (deltaX > 2.0f) break; // Success
}
```

### 3. Rope X-Alignment Fix
**File**: [UI/MainForm.cs](file:///d:/Full_end/C%23/ArtaleAI/UI/MainForm.cs)
- Increased threshold from 2.0f to 10.0f to engage precise alignment earlier.

### 4. Climb Down Fix
**File**: [Core/PathPlanningTracker.cs](file:///d:/Full_end/C%23/ArtaleAI/Core/PathPlanningTracker.cs)
- Dynamically selects "Up" or "Down" key based on entry position relative to rope top.

## Verification
- **Oscillation**: Character should now smoothly align X without jittering left/right, even when vertically distant from the target.
- **Logging**: Logs will show: `[移動] 點按: →, 距離=1.2 Pos=(60,175) Target=(61,172)`.
